{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-10752/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-10752"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:07:52"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man speaks angrily at a woman across from him."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-10752","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-10752"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1/14e5b3a4-8e91-47f0-be72-91ee4e9175e0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:08:20.260Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma states that she wanted “time” with Reynolds to herself, and he responds that she has him “all the time.” Time is a central theme in <em>Phantom Thread</em>. Near the end of the film, Alma says, in voiceover, “Sometimes I jump ahead in our life together, and I see a time near the end. I can predict the future, and everything is settled. And all our lovers and children and friends come back and are welcome. And we have large gatherings where everyone is laughing and playing games. I am older and I see things differently, and I finally understand you. I take care of your dresses, keeping them from dust and ghosts and time.” Alma, in short, seeks eternity with Reynolds. Being in control over their story therefore means taking command of time and being able to remain together forever. (Incidentally, Catherine Join-Diéterle says of the work of Cristóbal Balenciaga, one of the inspirations for Reynolds’s character, that it “bore a sense of eternity, of the reconciliation of past and present” (Join-Diéterle, “Dior and Balenciaga, 152).)</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10752/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:702.2283220720719,209.98592342342369,613.3375563063062,649.7043918918919"}}}]}]}]}